  "notes_sections": [
    "The probability mass function (PMF) of Poisson distribution is",
    ".. math:: f(k; \\lambda)=\\frac{\\lambda^k e^{-\\lambda}}{k!}",
    "For events with an expected separation :math:`\\lambda` the Poisson distribution :math:`f(k; \\lambda)` describes the probability of :math:`k` events occurring within the observed interval :math:`\\lambda`.",
